The Kogi State Command of the Nigeria Immigration Service has intercepted three trailer loads of travellers allegedly heading towards Ekiti for interrogation and profiling. Daily Trust learnt that the travellers, suspected to be illegal immigrants, were intercepted at Banda area of Lokoja by men of the Nigerian Navy on Tuesday night and handed over to the immigration officers yesterday. When Daily Trust visited the Kogi State Command of the Nigeria Immigration Service in Lokoja yesterday, the three trucks were seen parked in the area with some of the trucks loaded with foodstuffs and motorcycles. It was also observed that those intercepted were mostly men, women and children. When contacted, the Public Relations Officer of the Kogi State Command of the Nigerian Immigration Service, Mr Olasunkami Salami, said those intercepted were being profiled and promised to give further details.